es, numbers, and handwriting appear across the check, including a signature area, though most of the details are too small or blurred to read clearly. The check remains centered as a clean, flat product image, presenting the loan visually as an official bank document.\n\nThe scene changes to a red 1960s Ford Mustang driving through a bright, arid landscape. At first the rear-left side of the car fills much of the view. The car has squared-off rear lights, chrome trim, and a license plate that appears to read “1967.” It moves away along a pale road bordered by sand and low desert scrub. Through the rear window, a driver is faintly visible, but details of the person are indistinct.\n\nThe Mustang continues farther down the road, shrinking into the open desert. The surroundings are flat and sunlit, with low bushes scattered on both sides and a hazy horizon in the distance. The car’s red body stands out against the cream-colored sand and muted sky. Later it is seen from the front at an angle, driving toward and past the viewer’s side of the road. The Mustang emblem is visible in the center of the front grille, and the same “1967” plate is mounted below. The driver remains only a dark figure behind the windshield.\n\nThe commercial ends on a large outdoor sign for the bank, set against dark foliage with a bright glare of sunlight near the top. The sign reads “Chemical New York” in large white serif letters. Beneath it, smaller text reads “CHEMICAL BANK NEW YORK TRUST COMPANY.”",
